Van der Westhuizen represented his country 89 times during a decade-long career starting in 1993. TimesLIVE has compiled this timeline of the rugby legends life:1971 - Born, February, 201977 - starts primary school at Laerskool Derdepoort1980 July 12 - Attends first Springbok Test at Loftus when Boks lost 13-17 British &amp; Irish Lions1983 - starts High School at FH Odendaal, excels at athletics and rugby1987 - influential in guiding FH Odendaal to its first Administrators Cup final. They lose 18-14 to Hugenote from Springs. Hugenote contain future Springboks Japie Mulder and Chris Rossouw. With Van der Westhuizen there are three future 1995 World Cup winners in the match.1989-92 - plays for Tukkies.1992 March - makes provincial debut for Northern Transvaal against Transvaal in a Night Series friendly.1992 April - first-class debut for Northern Transvaal against Eastern Transvaal.1992 May - makes Currie Cup debut against Transvaal1992 August - plays for Junior Springboks against the touring All Blacks1993 April - represents Bok sevens at the World Cup in Edinburgh1993 May - makes Super 10 debut for Northern Transvaal1993 June/July - unused substitute for the Springboks in both Tests against the touring French</img>Joost van der Westhuizen. Image: Duif du Toit/Gallo Images Joost van der Westhuizen. Image: Duif du Toit/Gallo Images 1993 July - Makes Bok debut against Western Australia in Perth, scoring four tries1993 October - makes Test debut against Argentina and scores a try</img>Joost van der Westhuizen in action in 1994. Image: Gallo Images Joost van der Westhuizen in action in 1994. Image: Gallo Images 1995 June - influential as Boks win World Cup on home soil1995 November - marries first wife Marlene Terblanche1997/98 - Boks win 17 Tests in a row, Joost plays in 14 of those matches1998 - wins first Currie Cup with the Blue Bulls.</img> Joost van der Westhuizen and Ruben Kruger drinks from the cup after the Currie Cup final match between Blue Bulls (24) and Western Province (20) at Loftus Versfeld on October 31, 1998 in Pretoria, South Africa. Image: Duif du Toit/Gallo Images Joost van der Westhuizen and Ruben Kruger drinks from the cup after the Currie Cup final match between Blue Bulls (24) and Western Province (20) at Loftus Versfeld on October 31, 1998 in Pretoria, South Africa. Image: Duif du Toit/Gallo Images1999 - becomes Bok captain and leads them to the World Cup -October 2002, captain s Blue Bulls to Currie Cup title</img> This file photo taken on October 30, 1999 shows South African scrum-half and captain Joost Van Der Westhuizen (front) holding the ball during the Rugby World Cup semi-final match between Australia and South Africa at Twickenham stadium. Image: AFP PHOTO / Olivier MORINThis file photo taken on October 30, 1999 shows South African scrum-half and captain Joost Van Der Westhuizen (front) holding the ball during the Rugby World Cup semi-final match between Australia and South Africa at Twickenham stadium. Image: AFP PHOTO / Olivier MORIN</img> This file photo taken on August 02, 1999 shows South African President Thabo Mbeki (R) showing his rugby skills to the new captain of the Springboks Joost Van Der Westhuizen (L) at a training session in Johannesburg. Image: AFP PHOTO / ODD ANDERSENThis file photo taken on August 02, 1999 shows South African President Thabo Mbeki (R) showing his rugby skills to the new captain of the Springboks Joost Van Der Westhuizen (L) at a training session in Johannesburg. Image: AFP PHOTO / ODD ANDERSEN2002 - October marries singer Amor Vittone</img>South African celebrity couple Amor Vittone and Joost van der Westhuizen pose for a photo on July 22, 2005 in Pretoria. Image: Foto24/Gallo Images/Getty ImagesSouth African celebrity couple Amor Vittone and Joost van der Westhuizen pose for a photo on July 22, 2005 in Pretoria. Image: Foto24/Gallo Images/Getty Images2003 - plays in his third World Cup before retiring</img>This file photo taken on November 01, 2003 shows South African scrum-half Joost van der Westhuizen clearing the ball out of the scrum during the Rugby World Cup Pool C match between South Africa and Samoa at Lang Park in Brisbane. Image: AFP PHOTO / Greg WoodThis file photo taken on November 01, 2003 shows South African scrum-half Joost van der Westhuizen clearing the ball out of the scrum during the Rugby World Cup Pool C match between South Africa and Samoa at Lang Park in Brisbane. Image: AFP PHOTO / Greg Wood2009 - video emerges of a man having sex with a woman in film, there are claims it s Joost. He denies.2009 - Joost admits he was the man in the video.2011 - Diagnosed with MND2015 -inducted in Rugby Hall of Fame</img>Former South African Rugby World Cup winner team Captain Francois Pienaar (L) assisting his former teammate flyhalf Joost van der Westhuizen (Front), during a re-enactement of the team photo from the 1995 Rugby World cup victory on June 24, 2015 at Ellis Park in Johannesburg. Image: AFP PHOTO / GIANLUIGI GUERCIAFormer South African Rugby World Cup winner team Captain Francois Pienaar (L) assisting his former teammate flyhalf Joost van der Westhuizen (Front), during a re-enactement of the team photo from the 1995 Rugby World cup victory on June 24, 2015 at Ellis Park in Johannesburg. Image: AFP PHOTO / GIANLUIGI GUERCIA2017 - Dies age 45</img>Joost van der Westhuizen at Steyn City during a J9 foundation golf day on 10 November 2015. Image: Simphiwe Nkwali / Sunday Times. Joost van der Westhuizen at Steyn City during a J9 foundation golf day on 10 November 2015. Image: Simphiwe Nkwali / Sunday Times.